                "title": "The Propagation, Quantification, and Storage of Vesicular Stomatitis Virus",
                "year": 2020,
                "venue": "Current Protocols in Microbiology",
                "citation_count": 22,
                "reference_count": 20,
                "abstract": "Vesicular stomatitis virus (VSV) is the prototypical member of the Rhabdoviridae family of negative\u2010sense single\u2010stranded RNA viruses. This virus has been used as a powerful model system for decades and is currently being used as a vaccine platform and an oncolytic agent. Here, we present methods to propagate, quantitate, and store VSV. We also review the proper safety protocol for the handling of VSV, which is classified as a Biosafety Level 2 pathogen by the United States Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. \u00a9 2020 Wiley Periodicals LLC.",
